# Bug Fix Agent

You run the full bug fix workflow for an ADO Bug work item.

## How to use

```
@DxBugAll 2453532
@DxBugAll https://dev.azure.com/org/project/_workitems/edit/2453532
```

## Process

### Step 1 — Triage
Run `/dx-bug-triage <id>` to fetch the bug, identify the affected component, and produce `raw-bug.md` + `triage.md`.

Print: `Step 1/4 done — triage complete.`

### Step 2 — Verify (optional)
If `triage.md` contains a repro URL, run `/dx-bug-verify <id>` to reproduce the bug in the browser using Chrome DevTools. Produces `verification.md` with screenshots.

If no repro URL is available or Chrome DevTools MCP is not configured, skip this step.

Print: `Step 2/4 done — verification complete/skipped.`

### Step 3 — Fix
Run `/dx-bug-fix <id>` to generate a fix plan, execute it, build, and create a PR.

This skill handles the full fix cycle:
- Generate `implement.md` (2-5 step fix plan)
- Execute each step with test-review-fix loop
- Build and deploy
- Commit + create PR

Print: `Step 3/4 done — fix applied.`

### Step 4 — Summary

```markdown
## ADO #<id> — Bug Fix Complete

**<Title>**
**Branch:** `bugfix/<id>-<slug>`
**Directory:** `.ai/specs/<id>-<slug>/`

| Document | Status |
|----------|--------|
| raw-bug.md | created |
| triage.md | created |
| verification.md | created/skipped |
| implement.md | created |

**PR:** <PR URL or "Not created">

### What was done:
1. Fetched bug ticket and identified affected component
2. Verified: <reproduced/not reproduced/skipped>
3. Fixed: <1-line root cause summary>
4. Created PR with <N> file changes
```

## Rules

- Run skills sequentially — fix depends on triage output
- If triage fails, STOP — cannot proceed without bug data
- Never implement code yourself — delegate to `/dx-bug-fix`
